\title{Orthonormal basis}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-08}
\taxon{definition}

\p{Let #{V} be a finite-dimensional real vector space with a well-defined notion of a dot product. Let #{B} be an orthogonal basis of #{V}. We call #{B} an \define{Orthonormal Basis} of #{V} if for all #{f\in B} we also have #{f\cdot f=1}. In other words, we have for all #{f_{i},f_{j}\in B},
##{f_{i}\cdot f_{j}=\delta_{i,j}}
where #{\delta_{i,j}} is the Kronecker delta.}